{"lemma": "رِبْقٌ", "slug": "رِبْقٌ", "root": "ر.ب.ق", "root_slug": "ر-ب-ق", "root_link": "/words/roots/ر-ب-ق", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": false}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n14579"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%92%D9%82%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "cord", "fa": "بند", "ur": "رسمی", "tr": "bağ", "id": "tali", "bn": "দড়ি", "es": "cordel", "fr": "corde", "de": "Seil", "ru": "веревка", "zh": "绳索"}, "definition": null, "etymology": null, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n14579", "headword_ar": "رِبْقٌ", "root": "rbq", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A cord having in it a number of loops wherewith lambs,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "kids, are tied,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "made fast; any one of which loops is termed"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "riboqapN", "text_ar": "رِبْقَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb, K) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raboqapN", "text_ar": "رَبْقَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a cord which is doubled in the form of a ring, into which is put the head of a sheep"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "goat, and which is then tied,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "made fast:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so, says Az, I have heard from the Arabs of the desert of Benoo-Temeem: (TA:) pl. [of mult.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ribaAqN", "text_ar": "رِبَاقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ribaqN", "text_ar": "رِبَقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and [of pauc.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^arobaAqN", "text_ar": "اَرْبَاقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, K.) ―         -b2-  Hence, (TA,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xalaEa", "text_ar": "خَلَعَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA_isolaAmi mino Eunuqihi", "text_ar": "الاـِسْلَامِ مِنْ عُنُقِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "riboqapa", "text_ar": "رِبْقَةَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Msb, TA,) occurring in a trad., (S,) (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He cast off the tie of El-Islám,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb, TA,) with which he had bound himself, (TA,) ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from his neck."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] (Msb, TA. [See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xalaEa", "text_ar": "خَلَعَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lakumu AlEahodu maA lamo taA^okuluwA Alr~ibaAqa", "text_ar": "لَكُمُ العَهْدُ مَا لَمْ تَاْكُلُوا الرِّبَاقَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", also occurring in a trad., (S,) meaning (tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The covenant is yours"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "as long as ye sever not the tie with which ye are bound;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "this tie being likened to the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "riboq", "text_ar": "رِبْق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "upon the necks of lambs or kids; and the severing thereof, to the beast's eating its"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "riboq", "text_ar": "رِبْق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and severing it; for thereby the beast becomes free from the tie. (TA.) And in a trad. of 'Omar,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Huj~uwA biAl*~ur~iy~api laA taA^okuluwA A^arozaAqahaA wata*aruwA A^arobaAqahaA fiY", "text_ar": "حُجُّوا بِالذُّرِّيَّةِ لَا تَاْكُلُوا اَرْزَاقَهَا وَتَذَرُوا اَرْبَاقَهَا فِى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aEonaAqihaA", "text_ar": "اَعْنَاقِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Perform ye the pilgrimage with the women: devour not their means of subsistence, while ye leave their ties upon their necks"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: he likens the obligations imposed upon them to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ArbAq", "text_ar": "ارباق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) One says also, ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hal~a riboqatahu", "text_ar": "حَلَّ رِبْقَتَهُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He removed from him his anxiety:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA:) and so ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaTaEa riboqatahu", "text_ar": "قَطَعَ رِبْقَتَهُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "Msb", "K", "TA"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}